t": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "sociableness, socialness, familiarity, companionableness, companionship, fellowship, friendship,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "amity:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "syn."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^ulofapN", "text_ar": "اُلْفَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": as in the saying,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^adaAma A@ll~`hu jumoEapa maA bayonakumaA", "text_ar": "اَدَامَ ا@للّٰهُ جُمْعَةَ مَا بَيْنَكُمَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "May God make permanent the state of union,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "&c.,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "subsisting between you two"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (Aboo-Sa'eed, K.) ―         -b2-  Hence, (Mgh,)"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "yawomu AljumoEapi", "text_ar": "يَوْمُ الجُمْعَةِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (S, Mgh, Msb, K,) the original form, (TA,) of the dial. of 'Okeyl; (Msb, TA;) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "yawomu AljumuEapi", "text_ar": "يَوْمُ الجُمُعَةِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (S, Msb, K,) the most chaste form, (TA,) of the dial. of El-Hijáz; (Msb, TA;) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "yawomu AljumaEapi", "text_ar": "يَوْمُ الجُمَعَةِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (Msb, K,) of the dial. of Benoo-Temeem; (Msb, TA;) and, in consequence of frequency of usage,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AljumaEapu", "text_ar": "الجُمَعَةُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "alone; (Mgh;)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A well-known day;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K;) ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the day of the congregation;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "i. e."}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Friday;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] formerly called (TA)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the day of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlEaruwbap", "text_ar": "العَرُوبَة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (S, TA:) called"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "ywm AljmEp", "text_ar": "يوم الجمعة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "because of the congregating of the people thereon: (Msb:) Th asserts that the first who named it thus was Kaab Ibn-Lu-eí; and he is related to have said that it was thus called because Kureysh used to gather themselves together to Kuseí, [on that day,] in [the building called]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "daAru Aln~adowapi", "text_ar": "دَارُ النَّدْوَةِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (TA:) accord. to the R, Kaab Ibn-Lu-eí was the first who collected a congregation on the day of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlErwbp", "text_ar": "العروبة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", which was not called"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AljmEp", "text_ar": "الجمعة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "save since the coming of El-Islám; [or it was not generally thus called before El-Islám; for it is added,] and he was the first who named it"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AljmEp", "text_ar": "الجمعة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; for Kureysh used to congregate to him on this day, and he used to preach to them, and to put them in mind of the mission of the apostle of God, informing them that he should be of his descendants, and bidding them to follow him and to believe in him: (TA:) or, as some say, it was thus called in the time of El-Islám because of their congregating [thereon] in the mosque: accord. to a trad., the Ansár named it thus, because of their congregating thereon: (TA:) or it was thus named because God collected thereon the materials of which Adam was created: (I 'Ab:) those who say"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AljumaEapu", "text_ar": "الجُمَعَةُ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "regard it"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "as an epithet, meaning that this day collects men much; comparing it to"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "humazapN", "text_ar": "هُمَزَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "lumazapN", "text_ar": "لُمَزَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "DuHakapN", "text_ar": "ضُحَكَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (TA:) the pl. is"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "jumaEN", "text_ar": "جُمَعٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, Mgh, Msb, K) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "jumoEaAtN", "text_ar": "جُمْعَاتٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Msb, K) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "jumuEaAtN", "text_ar": "جُمُعَاتٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, Mgh, Msb, K) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "jumaEaAtN", "text_ar": "جُمَعَاتٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; (Msb, K;) of which the last is pl. of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "jumaEapN", "text_ar": "جُمَعَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", [as well as of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "jumoEapN", "text_ar": "جُمْعَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", accord. to analogy,] but not so"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "jumaEN", "text_ar": "جُمَعٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(AHát) [nor either of the other pls. mentioned above]. ―         -b3-  In like manner you say"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "SalaApN AljumoEapi", "text_ar": "صَلَاةٌ الجُمْعَةِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The prayer of Friday"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "], and, in consequence of the frequency of usage,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AljumoEapu", "text_ar": "الجُمْعَةُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "alone. (Mgh.) ―         -b4-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AljumoEapu", "text_ar": "الجُمْعَةُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", with the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "m", "text_ar": "م"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "quiescent, is also a name for ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The week;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "i. e.]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the days of the week"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "collectively"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]; of which the Arabs are said, by IAar, to have reckoned the Sabbath ("}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Als~abot", "text_ar": "السَّبْت"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[i. e. Saturday]) as the first, though they called Sunday the first of the days. (Msb.) ―         -b5-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "jumoEapN", "text_ar": "جُمْعَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is also"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "syn. with"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "majomuwEapN", "text_ar": "مَجْمُوعَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[meaning Things"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "collected together;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a collection"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "of things]; (K;) as in the phrase"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "jumoEapN mino HaSFY", "text_ar": "جُمْعَةٌ مِنْ حَصًى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a collection of pebbles"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (TA.) ―         -b6-  You say also"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "jumoEapN", "text_ar": "جُمْعَةٌ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mino tamorK", "text_ar": "مِنْ تَمْرٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A handful of dates."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, K.)"}], "source_refs": ["Mgh", "S", "Msb", "K", "TA"]}]}, "classical_definitions": null, "translations_attribution": {"model": "qwen36-35b-heretic", "generated_date": "2026-05-18", "pipeline_version": "words.translation.v1.spark"}}